quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  35,1,"All praise be to Allah, the Fashioner of the heavens and earth, Who appointed angels as His message bearers, having two, three, four wings. He adds to His creation whatever He pleases. Verily Allah has power over everything."{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3
  35,2,"Whatever Mercy Allah accords to people, none can withhold; and whatever He withholds, no other will be able to release after Him. He is Most Mighty, Most Wise."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  35,3,"O people, remember Allah's favour upon you. Is there any creator, apart from Allah, who provides you your sustenance out of the heavens and earth? There is no god but He. Whither are you, then, being misdirected?"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2